Ingredients:

Broth:
1 1/2 tablespoons chicken broth
1/4 inch piece ginger
1/4 teaspoon soy sauce
Wontons:
1 teaspoon ground pork
1/8 teaspoon soy sauce
1/4 teaspoon chives
1/8 teaspoon rice vinegar
1/4 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon grated ginger
Pinch crushed red pepper flakes
3 tiny wonton wrappers
Green onions, to garnish

Steps:

1. In a pot, heat all broth ingredients.

2. In a bowl, combine ground pork, soy sauce, chives, rice vinegar, cornstarch, grated ginger and red pepper flakes. Place a tiny pinch of pork mixture in the center of each wonton. Paint one corner with water and fold another corner on top of it. Place in broth and simmer for 4 minutes. Garnish with chives.

____________________________________

Ingredients:

Persian cucumber slices, cut into triangles
Yogurt & dill spread
1-inch pieces of bread
1-inch pieces smoked salmon
Caviar
Radish slices, cut into triangles
1 tablespoon butter
Tiny scones
Whipped cream
A very small amount of jam

Steps:

1. Top one piece of bread with yogurt/dill spread and cucumber triangles.

2. Top another piece of bread with yogurt/dill spread and smoked salmon and caviar.

3. Top another piece of bread with butter and radish triangles.

4. Arrange tea sandwiches on a plate along with tiny scones, whipped cream and jam. Enjoy with your tea!

Ingredients:

1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise
1/2 teaspoon ketchup
1/8 teaspoon chopped dill pickles
1/8 teaspoon mustard
Salt and pepper
Pinch sugar
Dash apple cider vinegar
1/2 teaspoon sliced onion
1/8 teaspoon oil
Oil for frying
1 tiny potato, cut into thin fries
1 tiny piece American cheese, melted

Steps:

1. In a small bowl, combine mayo, ketchup, pickles, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.

2. Sauté onion in 1/8 teaspoon oil until caramelized.

3. Heat oil in a pot and cook fries. Place cheese on top of fries as soon as they are done. Top with caramelized onions and sauce.

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon water, divided
1/2 teaspoon sugar
1/2 teaspoon butterfly pea flowers
1 teaspoon fresh squeezed lemon juice

Steps:

1. In a saucepan, add half the water and butterfly pea flowers and bring to a simmer.

2. Allow to steep for 10 minutes.

3. Combine remaining water and lemon juice. Strain the pea flower water and stir in sugar, add to a pitcher, pour lemon water over the top.

4. Watch the color begin to change and then stir to combine.

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon milk
1/2 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon sugar
1 vanilla bean, split and scraped
1 wedge of lemon
1-inch piece of pie dough
1/4 teaspoon raspberry jam
1 raspberry, blackberry and strawberry
Mint leaf and whipped cream, for garnish

Steps:

1. Add milk to a saucepan with sugar and cornstarch. Whisk to combine.

2. Add vanilla bean and squeeze in lemon juice and add lemon zest. Transfer mixture to a dish and place in refrigerator to cool.

3. Roll out pie dough and press into pie pan. Fill with dried beans. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 minutes. Remove beans.

4. Spread a layer of jam on the pie crust and top with pudding. Top with fresh berries, whipped cream and a mint leaf.

Ingredients:

1 teaspoon butter
1/4 teaspoon olive oil
1/4 teaspoon chopped onion, chopped
1/2 tiny garlic clove, chopped
Salt and pepper
1 tablespoon shredded cheddar
1 tablespoon sour cream
1 teaspoon herbs (thyme, parsley, chives)
1-inch ball of pie dough
3 tiny asparagus stalks

Steps:

1. In a pan, add butter, olive oil, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Saute 3 minutes.

2. In a small bowl, mix the shredded cheese, sour cream and herbs.

3. Roll out dough into a rectangle and place on a parchment-lined baking sheet.

4. Spread out the sour cream mixture on top of the dough, then add the onion and garlic.

5. Lay the asparagus on top and bake at 375 degrees for 7 to 8 minutes.

1/2 quail egg, whisked
1 tablespoon cornstarch
1 small potato, cut into fries
1 tablespoon mayonnaise

Lemon, to garnish

Ingredients:

Broth:
1 1/2 tablespoons chicken broth
1/4 inch piece ginger
1/4 teaspoon soy sauce
Wontons:
1 teaspoon ground pork
1/8 teaspoon soy sauce
1/4 teaspoon chives
1/8 teaspoon rice vinegar
1/4 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon grated ginger
Pinch crushed red pepper flakes
3 tiny wonton wrappers
Green onions, to garnish

Steps:

1. In a pot, heat all broth ingredients.

2. In a bowl, combine ground pork, soy sauce, chives, rice vinegar, cornstarch, grated ginger and red pepper flakes. Place a tiny pinch of pork mixture in the center of each wonton. Paint one corner with water and fold another corner on top of it. Place in broth and simmer for 4 minutes. Garnish with chives.

Ingredients:

1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise
1/2 teaspoon ketchup
1/8 teaspoon chopped dill pickles
1/8 teaspoon mustard
Salt and pepper
Pinch sugar
Dash apple cider vinegar
1/2 teaspoon sliced onion
1/8 teaspoon oil
Oil for frying
1 tiny potato, cut into thin fries
1 tiny piece American cheese, melted

Steps:

1. In a small bowl, combine mayo, ketchup, pickles, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.

2. Sauté onion in 1/8 teaspoon oil until caramelized.

3. Heat oil in a pot and cook fries. Place cheese on top of fries as soon as they are done. Top with caramelized onions and sauce.

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon milk
1/2 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon sugar
1 vanilla bean, split and scraped
1 wedge of lemon
1-inch piece of pie dough
1/4 teaspoon raspberry jam
1 raspberry, blackberry and strawberry
Mint leaf and whipped cream, for garnish

Steps:

1. Add milk to a saucepan with sugar and cornstarch. Whisk to combine.

2. Add vanilla bean and squeeze in lemon juice and add lemon zest. Transfer mixture to a dish and place in refrigerator to cool.

3. Roll out pie dough and press into pie pan. Fill with dried beans. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 minutes. Remove beans.

4. Spread a layer of jam on the pie crust and top with pudding. Top with fresh berries, whipped cream and a mint leaf.
